Cases were codified using the ICD-O-3 (7) and grouped according to the WHO 2008 classification (4) (
Table 1
). In brief, LNs were grouped into five broad categories: Hodgkin lymphomas, precursor lymphoid neoplasms, mature B-cell neoplasms, mature T-cell and NK-cell neoplasms and lymphoid neoplasms, NOS.
